verbose_text: Further, primary cells and in vivo mouse models are not robust systems for studying the role of FcgammaRIIIa in dengue infections because FcgammaRIIIa is unstable on primary monocytes / macrophages that are cultured ex vivo, and mouse models that are humanized for FcgammaR expression, and thus express FcgammaRIIIa, are immunocompetent, rendering them incompatible with current dengue infection models.
